				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">AA I would have liked to see.<a name="64628"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 28 04 11:09 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span> An AA to reduce casting time by a small percentage or to extend song length by a small percentage. Maybe 10% or so would make it easier to keep 4 songs up. I don't see how this is overpowering or unbalancing. We haven't gotten a really nice AA since fading memories. Our 66-70 songs are if anything a step down from what we had on a level by level basis. 
<br />
 Just enough tweaking to the cast or song length would let us do what we are already for the most part are doing now, just more reliably. It would make us able to mezz 3 mobs a bit easier. 
<br />
 I am sure that song length and casting time have been discussed before but the game has changed in the last couple of expansions and I feel bards have been getting the short end of the stick. Some of us will never be in plane of time or other high end zones. A usefull AA that makes us a bit more effective would be a nice way to advance our class without itemization. I would spend 9 aa points easily for this ability.
<br />
 I would like to hear pro's and con's of what this would bring to the game.</span></td>
