				<td colspan="2"><span>Err, no actually the thing that was meant was that the minimum duration of a lasting effect is 1 tick equaling 0 to 6 seconds. A spell's duration can only be specified in ticks (differing from disciplines which are not on a tick timer).
<br />
So a 10% increase in song duration wouldn't work as the smalles increase in song duration you could give a bard would be 33%. That would equal an increase in duration from 3 ticks to 4 ticks. So before a bard could purchase a 10% increase in duration, the whole spellsystem would have to be rewritten.
